This paper is about a new method for credit assignment in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the properties of the method and provides a theoretical analysis of its variance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The method could also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) due to its focus on efficient credit assignment.
